    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.33) leading the charge as our primary engine for offensive production. **Mickey Moniak** draws an exceptional matchup against Sasaki, where his 14% park bump and significant platoon advantage turn a base projection of 56.28 into an elite-tier start. Similarly, **Corbin Carroll** remains a core anchor; despite a tougher matchup against Gausman, his dynamic platoon edge and second-spot placement in the order capitalize on his elite speed profile, which is critical for our 5x5 objectives. **Max Muncy** (71.26) is our highest-rated infielder today, benefiting heavily from a porous Schultz (6.23 xERA) and the favorable hitting environment, making him a must-start at the MI spot.\n\nWhile the top of the lineup is robust, we face some volatility in the lower third. **Jose Caballero** (52.65) and **Austin Riley** (55.10) hover near the marginal threshold. **Jose Caballero** is fighting a tough matchup against the crafty Ragans, and while his platoon edge provides a slight buffer, he remains a candidate to be limited by his #8 spot in the order. **Austin Riley** is currently a speculative play pending final lineup confirmation; his score is hampered by an elite arm in Painter and a slight penalty for facing an elite defensive catcher. The most difficult bench decision involved **Alex Freeland** (52.07), who pushed hard for a spot but ultimately sits behind the higher offensive ceilings of our active starters. We are also wary of **Luis Campusano** (34.25), who remains well below our minimum efficiency floor of 40.0 and will be benched to protect our game caps until his matchup profile improves significantly.",
